@PavelDAS Have you fixed that problem？I had the same problem with my exceljs version "^4.4.0"。Here is my code：
`let excel_path = args.excel_path;
 let sheet_name = args.sheet_value;
 const workbook = new Workbook();
 await workbook.xlsx.readFile(excel_path);` 
only a few excel files will trigger this error，others will not. 
If you fixed that, please give me some advise, thx :)

node_modules\exceljs\lib\xlsx\xform\sheet\worksheet-xform.js
~465

`      if (rel.Type === RelType.VmlDrawing && model.comments && model.comments.length) {
        const vmlComment = options.vmlDrawings[rel.Target].comments;
        model.comments.forEach((comment, index) => {
          comment.note = Object.assign({}, comment.note, vmlComment[index]);
        });
      }
`
      
      add if:
      
`
      if (rel.Type === RelType.VmlDrawing && model.comments && model.comments.length) {
		if (typeof options.vmlDrawings[rel.Target] !== 'undefined') {
			const vmlComment = options.vmlDrawings[rel.Target].comments;
			
			model.comments.forEach((comment, index) => {
          comment.note = Object.assign({}, comment.note, vmlComment[index]);
        });
		}

      }
`
